## REVIEW
- 8-dim HITL checklist (Confidence Handling added in v6):
    Correctness · Safety · Idempotency · Observability · Cost ·
    Schema Discipline (D6) · Per-PK Ordering (D7) · Confidence Handling (D9 — NEW)
- HITL_REVIEW-<artefact>.md committed; PASS at >=19/24 AND every dim >=2/3
- Confidence Handling — 5 sub-checks (0-3 each, max 15; pass ≥10/15):
    1. Confidence threshold EXPLICIT (numeric, env-driven, not "TBD")
    2. Low-confidence path NAMED (review queue / quarantine / default value)
    3. Confidence PERSISTED alongside prediction (downstream sees both)
    4. Threshold CALIBRATED (held-out labels in prod; trainer-calibrated in lab)
    5. Confidence-distribution ALERT (CW metric; Day 10 wires alarm)
- Schema Discipline checks: carry from v3 (partition pruning, columnar projection,
  no JSON in curated/, etc.)
- Per-PK Ordering checks: carry from v4 (deterministic PK; SequenceNumberForOrdering)
- 12-layer prompt (NEW): prompts/v12_model.txt includes MODEL CONTEXT layer slot
- ASL Catch semantics:
    Use Catch for ERRORS (Lambda exceptions, States.TaskFailed)
    Use Choice for DATA-DRIVEN ROUTING (low_confidence flag, event_type, etc.)
    Never raise to route on data.
- IAM: NEVER wildcards; named verbs + ARN-scoped resources.
- Region: every CLI uses --region ap-south-1.
- Synthetic data only.
